cheap easy ideas for a year old girls birthday party my daughter just turned and i am trying to think of a good theme that will be cheap and easy for her birthday party this weekend i've racked my brain and can't come up with anything help i did a fairy party for my daughter at our house we wrote on the invitation for all the girls to wear their princess dresses i ordered fairy wings in bulk from birthday express or oriental trading when the girls arrived i told them they were fairies in training we had a little scavenger hunt where they had to work as a team to find the clues so that they could earn their wings and become real fairies the last clue led them to the stash of wings the girls wore the wings for the rest of the party and took them home as favors we also made fairy wands as a craft a couple days before the party i bought a bunch of dowel rods from the local craft store and painted them silver and i used a hot glue gun to glue foam stars to the tips of the dowal rods at the party i let the girls decorate the stars on their wands i put glitter and shiny beads in bowels on a table and let them glue them on to the wands once they were done i sprayed the wands with a little sealant to hold the glitter in place they also took their wands home as favors my daughter loved it her friends had a great time and her friends parents loved that the girls got to be creative and make their own wands it was cheap because we had it at our house and didn't have to worry about the fees to rent venues etc and that way you're in total control of the food that is served etc we served a number of healthy options Comanche Avenue Q The Inside The Amazing Race The Fairly OddParents The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe Teen Girl Squad Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban (film) Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban Magical objects in Harry Potter Spidey Super Stories Link (Legend of Zelda) Cardcaptor Sakura Ron Weasley Humphrey Bogart Upholstery Wand Paul Is Dead Rent (musica